MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis - Class in uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.analyses
 
MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis(File, File, File, File, File, File, File, File, File, File, String, TreeSet<String>, int, int, boolean) - Constructor for class uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.analyses.MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis
Deprecated. This constructor (and most of this class) initially cloned from one of the other uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.analyses (probably MultiHnCongruenceAnalysisNoCDFSitewiseLikelihoodOutputTemp). As a result, it takes a variety of arguments (treefileH0, treefileH1.. treefileH3 etc for example) pertaining to analyses with a fixed number of phylogenies (4) as this was the prototype specification (April 2011-Summer 2012).

These, fixed-number-of-topologies-variables, were then analysed via the deprecated MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis.go() method.

Both this constructor / these variables, and the MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis.go() method are deprecated. Instead, a MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis should be instantiated using the multi-tree constructor and variables, MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis(File dataSet2, File mainTreesFile, File constraintTreeFile, File labelledTreesFile, File workDir2, File binaries, String runID2, TreeSet taxaList2, String[] modelsList2, int thisFilter, boolean doFactor), and analysis called with the MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis.run() method, as this allows for phylogeny sets of arbitary length.
MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis(File, File, File, File, File, File, String, TreeSet<String>, String[], int, boolean) - Constructor for class uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.analyses.MultiHnCongruenceAnalysis
